Bring a #medium pot{} of @water{for boiling} to a boil. Add @brown rice{1/2%cup} and cook until tender, about ~{35%minutes}. Drain.

Peel @ginger{1%thumb}, then mince or finely grate. Trim woody bottom ends from @asparagus{6%ounce}, then cut into 2-inch pieces. Thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced), keeping greens and whites separate. Cut off and discard root ends of @baby bok choy{2}, then separate into individual stalks. Cut @lime{1} into wedges.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add asparagus and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, tossing, until tender, ~{4-6%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside. Add bok choy and another drizzle of oil to pan. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, tossing, until tender-crisp, ~{3-5%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Add @edamame{4%ounce}, scallion whites, and a drizzle of oil to same pan and cook until warmed through and lightly browned, ~{2-4%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside. Meanwhile, stir together @sour cream{2%tablespoon} and @water{2%tablespoon} in a #small bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in @wasabi paste{1%teaspoon} (to taste)—start with a pinch and go up from there.

Once rice is done, heat another drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in same pan. Add ginger, @sesame oil{1%tablespoon}, and @soy sauce{1%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add rice, season with salt and pepper, and toss to coat.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with asparagus, bok choy, and edamame. Sprinkle with scallion greens, @cashews{1%ounce}, and @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}. Drizzle with crema. Serve with lime wedges for squeezing over.

> Every element of this recipe brings something to feel good about: fiber-rich brown rice provides the base, while asparagus and bok choy add their vitamin-rich green veggie flair. Edamame has minerals like iron and magnesium, and cashews are a good source of healthy, unsaturated fats. Even the wasabi crema on top, with its prickly, peppery kick, will wake your senses and make you feel invigorated, energized, and pumped up.